        "markup": "<p><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: 'Cambria',serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: 'MS Mincho'; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-fareast; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;\">California employees are entitled to a minimum of 24 hours (3 days) of paid sick leave annually, regardless of actual accrual. Accrual remains at 1 hour per 30 hours worked, and unused sick leave carries over to the following year. Employers may limit usage to 48 hours annually.</span></p>",
